VerbBasedAnswerer
/ %!data% is overwritten by every action's result, so capture the channel
/ input (the question text) into a local %access% first. Subsequent steps
/ branch on %access% — stable for the whole goal.
- set %access% = %!data%
- if %access% contains 'write' then return "y"
- if %access% contains 'delete' then return "n"
- if %access% contains 'read' then return "a"
- return "n"
